The FactHarbor **[[Verein>>https://github.com/robertschaub/FactHarbor/blob/main/Docs/Legal/DRAFT_Vereinsstatuten_FactHarbor_DE.md]]** is currently in preparation. The legal structure is therefore best understood as planned rather than already established.
)))

== The FactHarbor Application ==

(% class="box infomessage" %)
(((
**FactHarbor analyzes claims and articles** by breaking them into verifiable pieces and collecting supporting and opposing evidence from web sources and databases.

It evaluates evidence quality and source reliability, then compares, challenges, and reconciles findings through a structured multi-agent AI debate.

**The result: a transparent verdict where every conclusion links to cited evidence — so you can judge for yourself.**
)))

----

== Why This Matters ==

People are losing trust — not just in specific claims, but in the ability to know what is true at all. Misinformation spreads faster than corrections can follow, and existing tools are manual, slow, and opaque.

At the same time, the infrastructure is shrinking:
* **Meta** exited the US Third-Party Fact-Checking Program (January 2025).
* **Google** reduced ClaimReview visibility in Search results (2025).
* Fact-checking organisations lost significant platform funding.

The sector needs independent, sustainable infrastructure that no single platform controls. FactHarbor is built for that: open-source, non-profit, and transparent.

----

== How It Works ==

Unlike single-model AI tools, FactHarbor uses a **structured multi-agent debate** — different AI providers argue for and against a claim, and only evidence-backed objections can change the verdict.

{{mermaid}}
flowchart TD
    subgraph MAIN [" "]
        direction LR
        INPUT(["Claim\nor Article"])
        A["Extract verifiable\nstatements"]:::ai

        B["Search supporting\nand opposing evidence"]:::web

        Q["Filter quality\nand score sources"]:::ai
        C["Organize and\ncluster evidence"]:::ai

        subgraph DEBATE ["Structured AI Debate"]
            direction TB
            D["Advocate"]:::ai
            SC["Self-Consistency"]:::ai
            E["Challenger"]:::ai
            F["Reconciler"]:::ai
            V["Validator"]:::ai
            D --> SC & E
            SC & E --> F --> V
        end

        OUTPUT(["Verdict and\nStructured Report"])

        INPUT --> A --> B --> Q --> C --> DEBATE --> OUTPUT
    end

    subgraph LEGEND ["Legend"]
        direction LR
        L1["AI-powered"]:::ai ~~~ L2["Web and External Sources"]:::web
    end

    MAIN ~~~ LEGEND

    style INPUT fill:#2196F3,stroke:#1565C0,color:#fff,stroke-width:2px
    style OUTPUT fill:#4CAF50,stroke:#2E7D32,color:#fff,stroke-width:2px
    style DEBATE fill:#FCE4EC,stroke:#C62828,color:#B71C1C
    style MAIN fill:none,stroke:none
    style LEGEND fill:#f9f9f9,stroke:#ccc,color:#666

    classDef ai fill:#E3F2FD,stroke:#1565C0,color:#0D47A1
    classDef web fill:#FFF3E0,stroke:#E65100,color:#BF360C
{{/mermaid}}

